OL,3,CBarry John: 'One of the greatest
OL,4,Csportsmen'
OL,6,FThe fly-half was born and grew up in
OL,7,FCefneithin, where he later went on to
OL,8,Fplay rugby as a school boy.
OL,10,F'A gifted player and a very good
OL,11,Ffriend'
OL,13,FSpeaking to ITV News Wales, Alan
OL,14,FEllis, the former chairman of
OL,15,FCefneithin RFC and "very good friend",
OL,16,Fdescribed the rugby legend as "a
OL,17,Fgifted player", and "somebody who
OL,18,Fcould speak eloquently about the game
OL,19,Fof rugby which he enjoyed and which he
OL,20,Fknew everything about."
